message.body: Happy birthday! What did you do today?
i slept through most of it, to be honest. had dinner with my parents and went to see gatsby. thanks for asking. :)
You're welcome. Good to know you can still take comas?! What did you have for dinner? Did you go out or stay in? Also is Gatsby a must see?

yeah, slept from 2 to 11 and napped from 1 to 5. nuts. panera for dinner, because we're not classy at all. gatsby was okay. it was a little much for me. my mom had never read the book, which i didn't know.
Wow. You must have needed all that sleep from finals! Have you enjoyed being home? Did you get any presents?

being home is great, i really needed a break from my real life. i got some cards and some "iou's" from family, but i sort of asked everyone to not give me anything. how was the end of the year for you?
I was very busy with finals and review sessions. And i'll be leaving for germany on tuesday! What kind of ious? Do you feel like you needed a break fromyour real life?

i hope your students did well on the final! my grandmother wants to send me some clothes, i think, and my dad is buying me bus tickets so i can visit some friends. everything was just getting to be a little too hectic, so i'm glad i'm here where there's almost nothing happening.
They did well! I'm pleased to know you're taking it easy. How does it feel not being a teenager anymore?
about the same? is it really supposed to feel that different?
probably not yet but i think it will. your twenties are an interesting time. Well. I'm going to head to bed. Happy birthday.
